Guests booking entire homes will face restrictions and must agree to an anti-party attestation, or risk being blocked from the platform.

description: Bangladesh celebrated its 54th Vijay Diwas, marking independence from Pakistan.  Chief Adviser Muhammad Yunus hailed the removal of Sheikh Hasina's government, calling it autocratic. Hasina, in exile, condemned Yunus and the interim government, accusing them of supporting anti-liberation forces and neglecting the war's legacy.  The traditional Victory Day parade was cancelled.
title: 'World's worst autocratic govt': Yunus targets Sheikh Hasina

description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi and Sri Lankan President Ranil Wickremesinghe held a joint press conference in New Delhi, emphasizing investment-led growth and connectivity as pillars of their strengthened partnership.  India pledged support for infrastructure projects, including electricity grid connectivity and a petroleum pipeline, alongside educational and training initiatives.  Wickremesinghe affirmed Sri Lanka's commitment to safeguarding Indian interests.
title: 'Emphasised investment-led growth': PM after post with Sri Lanka President

description: India's Jasprit Bumrah has called for patience as the team navigates a transitional phase with emerging players during the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Despite India's inconsistent performance, Bumrah has been a standout performer, taking 18 wickets. He emphasized the need for understanding and support for the less experienced bowlers adapting to challenging Australian conditions.
title: Bumrah urges patience with Team India in 'transition' mode

description: Michael Dell, CEO of Dell Technologies, advocates for a balanced work approach. He emphasizes working smarter, not harder, prioritizing sleep and incorporating humor into the workplace.  Dell encourages young professionals to experiment, take risks, and find valuable work while maintaining a healthy blend of work and personal life.
title: Dell CEO to employees overworking: ‘I learned long time ago that there's...’
Centre's air quality panel imposes GRAP III for Delhi-NCR

description: Congress leader Priyanka Gandhi carried a bag with "Palestine" written on it in Parliament.  The bag also featured a watermelon, a symbol of Palestinian solidarity.  This followed Gandhi's meeting with a Palestinian diplomat.  The BJP criticized the gesture as appeasement.  They said it was an attempt to grab headlines after election losses.
title: Priyanka brings 'Palestine bag' to Parliament; BJP calls it 'appeasement'

description: Prayagraj prepares for the 2025 Maha Kumbh, the world's largest religious gathering.  The event features enhanced infrastructure, extensive healthcare provisions, and heightened security measures.  Record-breaking attempts and environmental initiatives are planned, attracting global attention and academic study.
title: Maha Kumbh 2025: An immersive experience of religion, heritage & tradition

description: A tornado ripped through Scotts Valley, California, injuring four and causing widespread damage.  The twister, packing winds up to 144 km/h, left thousands without power.  Severe weather also impacted other states, with an ice storm fatality in Nebraska and heavy snow blanketing upstate New York and the Sierra Nevada.
title: Watch: Rare Tornado tears through California, flips cars and uproots trees

description: Mumbai captain Shreyas Iyer lauded Prithvi Shaw's natural talent while emphasizing the need for improved work ethic for the young batsman to reach his full potential. Iyer stressed personal responsibility and self-reflection as key to Shaw's development. He also praised Ajinkya Rahane's selfless contribution and leadership during Mumbai's Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy victory, highlighting the veteran's adaptability and dedication.
title: 'We can't babysit anyone': Shreyas Iyer on Prithvi Shaw

description: The Income Tax Department has recovered Rs 37,000 crore over the past 20 months from individuals who failed to file returns despite significant spending. Officials used data analytics and transaction records like luxury purchases to identify non-compliant taxpayers.
title: Taxpayers take note! Rs 37k cr from individuals not filing returns
How Indian teen rejected by Stanford is inspiring the internet: 'Tough loss, but ... '

description: Allu Arjun's "Pushpa 2" crossed ₹900 crore in India, despite a Monday slump.  The sequel saw a significant drop in collections after a strong second weekend, earning only ₹2.12 crore on its twelfth day.  However, the film's overall performance remains impressive, driven by strong Hindi, Telugu, and Tamil collections.
title: 'Pushpa 2' box office collection Day 12

description: India's wealthiest individuals, Mukesh Ambani and Gautam Adani, have recently seen their fortunes dip below $100 billion. Ambani's Reliance faces declining energy earnings and retail struggles, while Adani battles US investigations and the aftermath of fraud allegations.
title: India’s richest men, Ambani & Adani, drop out of $100 bn net worth: Report

description: Three broken idols, including one of Lord Ganesh and possibly Lord Kartikeya, were discovered during well excavation near a recently reopened Shiv-Hanuman temple in Sambhal, Uttar Pradesh. Sealed since the 1978 riots, the temple reopened on December 14th. Authorities secured the area for further excavation and held a prayer ceremony.
title: Watch: 3 idols recovered from well near Sambhal's Shiv-Hanuman temple

description: A Prime Minister's Museum member has appealed to Rahul Gandhi to retrieve letters written by Jawaharlal Nehru, including correspondence with Lady Mountbatten and Jayaprakash Narayan, allegedly removed on Sonia Gandhi's orders in 2008. The museum member, Rizwan Kadri, previously contacted Sonia Gandhi without response.
title: ‘Return Nehru's letters to Edwina Mountbatten': PM Memorial writes to Rahul

description: Cyclone Chido devastated Mayotte, a French territory in the Indian Ocean, potentially causing hundreds or even thousands of deaths. Rescue efforts are hampered by damaged infrastructure and the custom of quick burials. Hospitals and homes are severely damaged, with many injured. Aid is arriving from France and international organizations.
title: Cyclone Chido batters France's Mayotte; casualties might be in thousands

description: Israeli Prime Minister Netanyahu and US President-elect Trump held a discussion regarding the hostage crisis in Gaza and the situation in Syria. Netanyahu emphasized Israel's commitment to securing the release of hostages and achieving a decisive victory. He also warned Iran and Hezbollah against further actions, highlighting Israel's changing influence in the Middle East amidst the ongoing conflict with Hamas.
title: 'Complete Israeli victory': Details from Trump-Netanyahu's 'friendly' phone call

description: India faced early setbacks on Day 3 of the Brisbane Test as Starc and Hazlewood ripped through their top order. Jaiswal fell cheaply to Starc for the third time this series, highlighting his vulnerability against left-arm pace. Gill followed soon after, leaving India struggling after Australia posted a formidable 445, fueled by Head's 152 and Smith's century.
title: How Starc got rid of Yashasvi Jaiswal, Shubman Gill

description: Isa Guha apologised for referring to Jasprit Bumrah as the "Most Valuable Primate" during commentary.  The former England cricketer's remark, though intended as praise, sparked controversy due to its potential for misinterpretation, particularly given cricket's history with racial sensitivity. Guha expressed regret for any offense caused, emphasizing her commitment to equality and inclusion.
title: Isha Guha apologises for calling Bumrah 'primate', says...
Assad allegedly airlifted £200m of Syria’s wealth to Moscow: Report

description: As 2024 winds down, astrologers offer tailored guidance for each zodiac sign. From embracing patience to letting go of perfectionism, each sign has specific areas to focus on.  The stars encourage reflection, completion of projects, and setting intentions for a successful 2025.
title: What every zodiac should do before 2024 ends
Flyers’ wait to keep laptops in cabin bags for security checks gets longer

description: Virat Kohli's struggles continued in the third Test against Australia at the Gabba. After a promising century in the second Test, he fell cheaply for 3, edging a Hazlewood delivery to Carey. His dismissal triggered fan criticism, following low scores in the first and third Tests. His dismissal left fans frustrated, with many taking to social media to criticise his form and even calling for his retirement.
title: 'Virat Kohli should learn from Dhoni and retire'

description: Omar Abdullah and the Congress clashed over EVM reliability and INDIA bloc leadership. Abdullah criticized 'selective' EVM blaming and urged the Congress to earn its leadership role, advocating for consistent engagement within the alliance beyond election periods.  Congress retorted that other parties, not them, questioned EVMs, and they only addressed the Election Commission.
title: 'Why this approach after being CM?': Cong hits back at Omar's remark on EVM

description: Zomato received a Rs 803 crore GST notice.  The government says Zomato must pay tax on delivery fees. Zomato says it passes these fees to delivery partners.  The tax covers October 2019 to March 2022.
title: Explained: Why has Zomato received a Rs 803 crore GST demand notice?

description: A gang of four was arrested for kidnapping actor Mushtaq Khan from Delhi airport and holding him hostage for ransom.  They also plotted to kidnap Shakti Kapoor. Khan escaped, but the gang stole money from his account.  A suspect in comedian Sunil Pal's kidnapping was injured during a police encounter.
title: NCR gang involved in kidnapping film stars targeted Shakti Kapoor

description: Virat Kohli's persistent struggles with deliveries outside off-stump continue, particularly in Test matches. His predictable tendency to chase these deliveries has become a boon for bowlers, resulting in a string of dismissals. Despite the repeated failures, Kohli seems reluctant to abandon this high-risk approach, a stark contrast to Sachin Tendulkar's famous restraint at the SCG.
title: Virat Kohli and that corridor of certainty

description: World-renowned tabla maestro Zakir Hussain passed away at 73 in San Francisco due to complications from idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis.  A child prodigy, he rose to global acclaim, collaborating with both Indian and Western music legends. His innovative fusion music and captivating performances cemented his legacy as a cultural ambassador and earned him numerous awards, including four Grammys.
title: Tabla maestro Zakir Hussain no more: All you need to know about his life

description: Chinese President Xi Jinping acknowledged internal conflicts within the Communist Party as inevitable, emphasizing the need for discipline and purging negative influences.  His renewed anti-corruption campaign, revealed in a recent speech, continues to target officials, even loyalists, contributing to bureaucratic paralysis amid a slowing economy.  The party is now urging the removal of internal threats to solidify its legitimacy.
title: Xi Jinping says ‘inevitable’ for ruling party to have internal conflicts

description: South Korea's impeached President Yoon Suk Yeol faces investigation for insurrection after imposing martial law, deploying over 1,500 troops.  The Constitutional Court reviews his impeachment while ruling party leader Han Dong-hoon resigns, expressing no regret for supporting the impeachment. North Korea labels Yoon as the "ringleader of rebellion."  Prime Minister Han Duck-soo serves as interim leader during the court's deliberation.
title: 'Over 1,500 troops deployed during martial law': South Korea defence ministry

description: Infosys founder NR Narayan Murthy, speaking at the Indian Chamber of Commerce, championed technology urged entrepreneurs to adopt "compassionate capitalism" and stressed hard work.
title: Narayan Murthy wants young entrepreneurs to embrace compassionate capitalism

description: Perplexity AI CEO Aravind Srinivas, an IIT and UC Berkeley graduate, publicly questioned his three-year green card wait. Elon Musk supported Srinivas's plea.  The exchange sparked online debate about US immigration policies.  Srinivas proposed using technology to speed up the application process.  He suggested higher fees for faster service.  A green card offers benefits but involves complex procedures.
title: 'Should I get a green card?': Indian-origin CEO’s post goes viral, Musk replies

description: 18-year-old Indian chess prodigy Gukesh D has become the youngest world chess champion, but his victory comes with a Rs 4.67 crore tax bill, exceeding MS Dhoni's IPL salary. His Rs 11.34 crore prize money from the World Chess Championship triggers a hefty tax liability due to India's tax laws.
title: Gukesh to pay more taxes than Dhoni's current IPL salary

description: Virat Kohli's persistent dismissals outside off-stump in Australia raise concerns for India's Test aspirations.  His weakness, particularly early in his innings, has been exploited by bowlers.  Drawing inspiration from Sachin Tendulkar's unbeaten 241 in Sydney (2003-04), where he eschewed cover drives, Kohli could regain form.  Tendulkar's patience and adaptability offer a valuable lesson for Kohli to overcome this challenge.
title: What Kohli can learn from Sachin's Sydney masterclass

description: The National Payment Corporation of India (NPCI) has issued a warning about the "Digital Arrest" scam targeting users of digital payment platforms.  Criminals impersonate officials, using threats and demands for money.  NPCI advises verifying identities and reporting suspicious activity to the cybercrime helpline (1930).
title: NPCI warns UPI users about scam that Indians are losing crores to

description: India's struggles in the Border Gavaskar Trophy continued at the Gabba, with Australia posting a formidable first-innings total. Former Pakistan cricketer Basit Ali attributed India's woes to a disconnect between captain Rohit Sharma and coach Gautam Gambhir, citing inconsistent selection choices. India's bowling, heavily reliant on Jasprit Bumrah's six-wicket haul, faltered against Travis Head and Steve Smith's centuries.
title: 'Rohit Sharma and Gautam Gambhir not on the same page'

description: Mumbai captain Shreyas Iyer lauded Prithvi Shaw's natural talent while emphasizing the need for improved work ethic for the young batsman to reach his full potential. Iyer stressed personal responsibility and self-reflection as key to Shaw's development. He also praised Ajinkya Rahane's selfless contribution and leadership during Mumbai's Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy victory, highlighting the veteran's adaptability and dedication.
title: 'We can't babysit anyone': Shreyas Iyer on Prithvi Shaw

description: Tabla maestro Zakir Hussain passed away at 73 in the US on Monday. Prime Minister Narendra Modi mourned the loss, praising Hussain's revolutionary impact on Indian classical music and his ability to connect diverse genres. Hussain's illustrious career included collaborations with renowned musicians across the globe, leaving a lasting legacy on the world music scene.
title: 'Revolutionized Indian classical music': PM condoles Zakir Hussain's demise

description: Israel launched intense airstrikes in Syria's Tartus region, targeting military sites and reportedly devastating air defense and missile storage facilities. This marks the heaviest bombardment in the area since 2012. Israel claims the strikes are preemptive measures to thwart security threats, while Syria's de facto leader criticizes them as unprovoked aggression.
title: Watch: Israel drops 'earthquake bomb' on Syria, impact felt on Richter scale

description: Bitcoin soared to a new all-time high, fueled by President-elect Trump's pro-crypto stance and plans for US dominance in the sector.  The surge, exceeding $106,000, boosted the broader crypto market.  Trump's support for a national Bitcoin reserve and a friendlier regulatory environment are driving investor optimism and inflows into Bitcoin ETFs.
title: Bitcoin rises to record after longest weekly winning run since 2021

description: A 400-year-old Shiva and Hanuman temple, rediscovered during an electricity theft inspection in Sambhal district, has reopened after 46 years.  Authorities cleaned the premises, installed electricity and CCTV cameras, and performed a prayer ceremony.  The SDM plans to restore the original structure and appoint a caretaker. An ancient well was also uncovered during the operation.
title: 'Aarti' at reopened Shiva temple in Sambhal; admin aim to restore original design

description: Syrian rebels, led by Hayat Tahrir al-Sham, ousted President Bashar al-Assad, ending his family's decades-long rule.  The rebels are now leading a fragile transition, facing immense economic challenges and the threat of ISIS.  While Russia withdraws its forces, Israel continues airstrikes, adding to the nation's complex and uncertain future. How the new leadership, led by the insurgents, will govern the fractured nation.​​​​
title: Life in Syria After Bashar al-Assad: How will the rebels rule?
MAGA conspiracy theories link drone sightings to Project Blue Beam

description: Allu Arjun's "Pushpa 2" continues its box office rampage, crossing Rs 900 crore in India and ₹1200 crore globally in just ten days.  The film has now secured the third spot on the list of highest-grossing Indian films worldwide, surpassing "RRR."  Strong second-weekend earnings suggest further record-breaking potential.
title: Pushpa 2 day 11 collection: Film crosses Rs 900cr; beats RRR's this record
Was Kimberly Guilfoyle’s fashion style too much for Don Jr.?

description: Mysterious drones buzzing over the East Coast have sparked alarm and confusion.  Andrew Tate publicly asked Elon Musk for an explanation, while Musk criticized traditional fighter jets and championed AI-controlled drone warfare.  Residents report nightly sightings, and though officials offer reassurances,  public skepticism remains high.
title: Drones mystery: Andrew Tate demands answers from Musk - 'Explain ...'

description: Indian commercial banks wrote off Rs 12.3 lakh crore in loans between FY15 and FY24. Public sector banks accounted for Rs 6.5 lakh crore of write-offs in the last five years. Write-offs peaked in FY19 at Rs 2.4 lakh crore and fell to Rs 1.7 lakh crore in FY24. Banks continue recovery efforts despite write-offs, which do not waive borrower liabilities.
title: Rs 12 lakh crore loans written off in 10 yrs, half of it by PSU banks in last 5 yrs

description: Organizers of the Bidhannagar Mela Utsav in Kolkata have requested Bangladeshi traders to withdraw from the fair due to the ongoing unrest in Bangladesh.  Refunds are being issued for pre-booked stalls to prevent potential trouble and ensure the safety of the traders. The fair, featuring around 500 stalls, will proceed as planned from Tuesday to January 6th.
title: 'Don't come, we'll send you a refund', West Bengal fair tells Bangladesh traders

description: College football star Travis Hunter won the Heisman Trophy.  His fiancée, Leanna Lenee, caused a stir with her delayed reaction.  A video showed her seated while others celebrated Hunter's win.  This fueled existing fan concerns about their relationship.  Hunter defended Lenee, stating people are too invested.  The couple plan a 2025 wedding after the NFL draft.
title: Travis Hunter's fiancée Leanna sparks controversy with her unexpected reaction

description: Bengaluru police arrested a woman, her mother, and brother for allegedly abetting the suicide of the woman's husband, an automobile executive.  The trio were apprehended across multiple states and remanded to judicial custody. The deceased left behind extensive notes and a video, which police are investigating.
title: Bengaluru techie suicide: Atul's estranged wife was living as paying guest

description: Following the suicide of Atul Subhash, who blamed his wife and in-laws for harassment, his family seeks custody of his four-year-old son. They believe the child embodies Atul and provides solace for their grief.
title: 'He is junior Atul Subhash for them': Bengaluru techie's kin seek custody of his son
